parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key will not turn in the ignition
and the brake lights may not function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling or shut down of the engine can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts down without warning
and the electrical systems may still be functional.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: and the airbag system may not deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission to engage 1st gear properly can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when merging into traffic or crossing intersections.
symptoms: The vehicle pops out of 1st gear during acceleration
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the vehicle jerks back and forth when coming to a stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Clutch Failure - Clutch Spring Bracket Disengagement
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch spring bracket can cause the clutch to disengage, leading to loss of power and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The clutch spring bracket disengages from the vehicle
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure - Relay Control Module (RCM) Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the RCM can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of power and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: the vehicle's gears slip into first and second gear
causing the vehicle to shut off
vehicle not shifting out of park

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure - Total Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power completely, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: causing a total loss of power
the vehicle's gears slip into first and second gear
causing the vehicle to shut off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire failure can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries. Poor quality tires can compromise vehicle safety and performance.
Low-profile tires can be prone to damage from potholes and other road hazards, leading to bent rims and compromised vehicle safety.
The absence of a spare tire can leave drivers stranded in the event of a flat tire, compromising their safety and convenience.
symptoms: No spare tire provided with the vehicle.
